# Default policy: normalize all text files to LF in the repo, regardless of
# what the working-tree filesystem (WSL vs Windows tools) does. Without this,
# Windows tools (PowerShell, some editors) silently re-save text files with
# CRLF, producing phantom diffs on every commit. We're Linux-deployed end to
# end (Pi5 Docker, HA add-on, training in WSL), so LF is the right choice.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit binary markers — guards against git's text-detection occasionally
# guessing wrong on small/short binaries and trying to line-end-normalize them.
*.wav binary
*.onnx binary
*.tflite binary
*.db binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
